==French==
===Article===
'''le''' {{m}} ({{f}} '''[[la]]''', ''m and f plural'' '''[[les]]''')
[[Category:French articles]]
#[[the]]
#:''Le
#(''used before abstract nouns; not translated in English'')
#(''before parts of the body'') [[the]]; [[my]], [[your]], ''etc.''
#:''Il a une cicatrice à la visage'' — He has a scar on the face ''or'' He has a scar on his face
#:''Il s’est cassé la jambe'' — He has broken his arm
#(''before units'') [[a]], [[an]]
#:''cinquante kilomètres à l’heure'' — fifty kilometres an hour

====Usage notes====
#'''Le''' becomes '''l’''' before a vowel or an unaspirated h.
#:''l’amour'' — love
#:''l’homme'' — the man

===Pronoun===
'''le''' {{m}} ({{f}} '''[[la]]''', ''m and f plural'' '''[[les]]''')

#[[him]] (''direct object'')
#[[it]]
#(''used to refer to something previously mentioned or implied; not translated in English'')
#:''Je suis petit et lui, il l’est aussi'' — I am small and he is too (''"he is it too", i.e., "he is small too"'')


